Two random variables $$X$$ and $$Y$$ are distributed according to 
$$${f_{X,Y}}\left( {x,y} \right) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {\left( {x + y} \right),} &amp; {0 \le x \le 1,} &amp; {0 \le y \le 1}  \cr 
   {0,} &amp; {otherwise} &amp; \,  \cr 

 } } \right.$$$
<p>The probability $$P\left( {X + Y \le 1} \right)$$ is ________.</p>
